WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Tri' is a triangular-shaped board where a chain of 6 links
(that cannot be splitted) is displayed. The goal is to move the
links, following certain rules in order to match a pattern shown
at the upper right in the game window.

  Here's an example at the beginning of a game:

                             o

                           o   o

                         o   o   o

                       o   o   o   o
                      /             +
                     o - o - o - o - o

Note: the 'o' symbols represent the tiles on the board and
      the '/', '-' and '+' symbols represent the links.

  You cannot move the links to a tile already connected by other
links. However, you can link together the two ends of the chain.
But beware, because once these ends are 'glued' together, they
cannot be unglued... so connect them only when you are about to
match the pattern shown at the upper right, otherwise the game
may be impossible to complete.

  Have fun!

